The paper deals with query processing for RDF data, which is typically stored in graph databases. Therefore, cs.DB (database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Apache Spark, which is a distributed computing framework, making cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with big data problems, which could fall under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.IR (information retrieval). Finally, the paper proposes different approaches for query processing, which could fall under cs.AI (artificial intelligence) as well.
